          <strong>PICA - Display</strong><br>
          The exhibition project by artist Caecilia Lahutte Nims was developed within the teaching degree program at the Institute for Art Education at Goethe University Frankfurt.
          The focus was on sculpture and artistic spatial concepts under the supervision of Professor Leunora Salihu.
          For the exhibition theme “Perspective”, the display typeface PICA was created as an interface between type design, exhibition design and visual communication, inspired by the aesthetics of coded systems.
        </p>
